http://www.apo.data.faa.gov/atadsintro.htm

   [planeglobenew.jpg]

   The Air Traffic Activity Data System (ATADS) is the official source of
   historical air traffic activity for center, airport, and instrument
   operations counts, as well as counts of services provided by flight
   service stations. Monthly and annual counts are available on the
   following screens either by facility, state, region, or nationally.
   Some ranking tables are also available.
